article.description: Monica Wright scored 27 points Sunday to lead No. 17 Virginia to a 65-55 victory over Mount St. Mary's.
article.headline: Wright scores 27, Littles has first double-double as Cavs move to 5-0 at home
article.linkText: Wright, Littles help Virginia stay perfect at home
article.story:
CHARLOTTESVILLE, Va. -- Monica Wright scored 27 points Sunday to lead Virginia (No. 15 ESPN/USA Today, No. 17 AP) to a 65-55 victory over Mount St. Mary's.

Lyndra Littles had her first double-double of the season, scoring 11 and grabbing 10 boards for the Cavaliers (9-2). Wright scored at least 20 points for her sixth straight game and also made three steals.

Hassanah Oliver led the Mountaineers (5-5) with 14 points and Mary Dunn added 11.

Wright scored nine points in the final 5:54 of the half to give the Cavaliers a 27-23 lead. Virginia did not trail the rest of the way. Both teams shot poorly for the game -- 37 percent.

Virginia ran its home record to 5-0 this season and is now 6-0 all-time against the Mountaineers.
